        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Why Electric Vehicle Finance Is Different</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Electric vehicles are treated differently by lenders for several important reasons. Many lenders offer discounted green car loan rates — typically 0.3–0.7% lower than standard rates — because EVs qualify as environmentally friendly assets. The lowest rate currently available for an EV-eligible loan is 5.09% p.a. (comparison rate 5.78%) from RACV, compared to 5.49% for a standard new car loan.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Beyond rate discounts, the Australian Government's FBT exemption for eligible EVs under a novated lease can save employees thousands per year. This makes the total cost of ownership for an EV financed through a novated lease dramatically cheaper than it appears at sticker price. Nik Finance can help you assess whether a standard car loan, chattel mortgage, or novated lease is the best structure for your situation.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">EV sales in Australia are accelerating rapidly. In January 2026, 5,161 plug-in hybrids were sold (up 170.5% year-on-year), and petrol vehicle sales fell 14%. Around 40% of lenders in Australia now offer a specific discounted rate for electric or green vehicles.</p>
        </section>
