        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Standard Green Car Loan (Personal Use)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">A secured car loan at a discounted rate for qualifying electric or plug-in hybrid vehicles. Rates from 5.09% p.a. This is the simplest option for personal buyers — fixed repayments, you own the car, no employer involvement required.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Novated Lease With FBT Exemption (Salary Sacrifice)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The most tax-effective option for salaried employees. Lease payments and running costs are deducted from pre-tax salary. The FBT exemption means the full payment comes from pre-tax income with no fringe benefits tax payable. On a $60,000 EV with a $100,000 salary, savings can exceed $10,000–$15,000 over a 5-year lease compared to buying with a standard car loan after tax.</p>
        <div class="bg-[#0d4d3e]/5 border-l-4 border-[#10b981] rounded-r-lg p-6 my-6"><p class="text-[#0d4d3e] font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Important: from 1 April 2025, plug-in hybrid electric vehicles (PHEVs) are no longer eligible for the FBT exemption on new leases. Only battery electric vehicles (BEVs) and hydrogen fuel cell vehicles qualify for new arrangements. Existing PHEV leases entered before this date retain the exemption for the duration of their original lease term.</p></div>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Chattel Mortgage (Business Use)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">If you are self-employed or the vehicle is used primarily for business, a chattel mortgage lets you claim GST on purchase, deduct interest, and depreciate the vehicle. For a $65,000 EV, GST recovery alone is approximately $5,909. Combined with interest deductions and depreciation, the effective cost drops significantly.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">FBT Exemption — What You Need to Know (2026)</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The Electric Car Discount (Treasury Laws Amendment Act 2022) exempts eligible EVs from fringe benefits tax when provided through a novated lease. The key eligibility criteria are:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3 my-6">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Must be a battery electric vehicle (BEV) or hydrogen fuel cell vehicle</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Must be first held and used after 1 July 2022</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Must be below the luxury car tax threshold — currently $91,387 for fuel-efficient vehicles (FY 2025-26)</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Must be a passenger vehicle carrying less than 1 tonne and fewer than 9 passengers</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">PHEVs no longer eligible for new leases from 1 April 2025 (existing leases grandfathered)</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Motorcycles, scooters, and commercial vehicles are not eligible</span></li>
          </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The exemption covers the car fringe benefit and associated car expenses including fuel (electricity), registration, insurance, and servicing. A home charging station is not covered as an associated car expense. The government will review the exemption by mid-2027.</p>
